                </div>

                <div class="govuk-accordion__section">
                    <div class="govuk-accordion__section-header">
                        <h2 class="govuk-accordion__section-heading ukri-accordion__section-heading">

                            <button type="button" id="accordion-default-heading-4" aria-controls="accordion-default-content-4" class="govuk-accordion__section-button" aria-expanded="false">
                                How we will assess your application
                            </button><span class="govuk-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span></h2>
                    </div>
                    <div id="accordion-default-content-4" class="govuk-accordion__section-content" aria-labelledby="accordion-default-heading-4">
                        <p class="govuk-body">You must meet all the eligibility criteria and complete the other sections of the application satisfactorily. Applications which don’t adhere to these rules will be disqualified and will not progress further. Ineligible, incomplete, obscene or fraudulent entries will also be disqualified at this stage.</p>
                        <p class="govuk-body">The AHRC and the BBC will then assess all remaining applications against the assessment criteria below and assign an initial grade (1 to 6), where 1 is unsatisfactory and 6 is exceptional. After considering all proposals, both the AHRC and the BBC will each shortlist up to 60 applications.</p>

                        <p class="govuk-body">When deciding which candidates will be selected to go forward to attend the workshops, the judges will be looking for applications that:</p>

                        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                            <li>give a simple, jargon free explanation of the research in an engaging manner</li>
                            <li>demonstrate high standards of scholarship with originality and quality</li>
                            <li>are creative and original</li>
                            <li>provide a strong programme idea that explains the significance of the research and what the findings mean in day-to-day terms</li>
                            <li>have an editorial and stylistic suitability for a Radio 3 audience</li>
                            <li>have a review and research description that shows a breadth of interest</li>
                            <li>demonstrate that you are comfortable communicating ideas outside of your research area in an interesting, well-written and engaging manner</li>
                            <li>demonstrate ideas that are innovative, and interesting to a public audience.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="govuk-body">Unfortunately, due to the volume of applications, we are not able to provide individual feedback if you are unsuccessful at the application stage.</p>
